Syrup of lavender is very useful for persons with sickness of the nerves, especially from cold, and it is powerful against paralysis, spasm, epilepsy and debilitation of the nerves. It is not recommended for the elderly who are suffering from catarrh.

Syrup of mint is moderately warming. It warms a little, hence it improves digestion of the stomach and with its natural warmth, restores the debilitated and inactive stomach. It is said, 'Mint is never slow in the stomach.'

